qas.question: Under whose leadership did Yugoslavia become a founding member of the Non-Aligned Movement?
In what year did Tito co-found the Non-Aligned Movement?
Which Indonesian leader co-founded the Non-Aligned movement with Tito?
Who became the first Secretary General of the Non-Aligned Movement?

context: Under <a0_0>Tito<a0_0/>'s leadership, Yugoslavia became a founding member of the Non-Aligned Movement. In <a1_0>1961<a1_0/>, Tito co-founded the movement with <a2_0>Egypt<a2_0/>'s Gamal Abdel Nasser, India's Jawaharlal <a3_0>Nehru<a3_0/>, Indonesia's Sukarno and Ghana's Kwame Nkrumah, in an action called The Initiative of Five (Tito, Nehru, Nasser, Sukarno, Nkrumah), thus establishing strong ties with third world countries. This move did much to improve Yugoslavia's diplomatic position. On 1 September 1961, Josip Broz <a4_0>Tito<a4_0/> became the first Secretary-General of the Non-Aligned Movement.
